---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ProsePage from '../components/ProsePage.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for BMI Result — how we handle cookies, advertising, analytics, and your data."
>
  <ProsePage title="Privacy Policy" lead="Last updated: June 2026">

    <p>
      BMI Result ("we", "our", "the site") is operated at bmiresult.com. We respect
      your privacy. This policy explains what information is collected when you use this site, how it
      is used, and your choices.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">1. Information we collect</h2>
    <p>
      All BMI inputs (height, weight, age, gender) are processed entirely in your browser. We do not
      transmit or store these values on any server. No account is required.
    </p>
    <p>
      If Google Analytics is enabled, anonymous usage data — such as pages visited, session duration,
      browser type, and approximate geographic region — may be collected by Google according to their
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" class="text-(--color-link)" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a>.
      This data is aggregated and does not identify you personally.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">2. Advertising (Google AdSense)</h2>
    <p>
      We use, or intend to use, Google AdSense to display advertisements on this site. Google AdSense
      uses cookies and similar tracking technologies to serve ads that are relevant to your interests,
      based on your browsing activity across websites. These are third-party cookies set by Google.
    </p>
    <p>
      Google may use data from its advertising cookies to personalise ads shown to you. You can opt out
      of personalised advertising by visiting
      <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" class="text-(--color-link)" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a>
      or by visiting
      <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" class="text-(--color-link)" target="_blank" rel="noopener">aboutads.info</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      We comply with the
      <a href="https://support.google.com/adsense/answer/48182" class="text-(--color-link)" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google AdSense programme policies</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">3. Cookies and local storage</h2>
    <p>
      We use browser <strong>localStorage</strong> (not cookies) to store:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
      <li>Your unit preference (metric kg/cm vs US lb/ft)</li>
      <li>Your theme preference (dark or light mode)</li>
      <li>Your recent BMI history (last 5 results, stored only on your device)</li>
      <li>Whether you have accepted or declined the cookie consent notice</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Third-party services (Google Analytics, Google AdSense) may set their own cookies. You can
      control or delete cookies via your browser settings at any time.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">4. Data sharing</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data with any third party. Aggregate, anonymised
      analytics data may be shared with Google as part of using their services. We have no access to
      the ad-targeting data collected by Google.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">5. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      If you are in the EU/EEA or UK, you have rights under GDPR and UK GDPR, including the right to
      access, correct, or delete personal data. Since we do not collect personal data on our servers,
      most GDPR requests can be fulfilled by clearing your browser's localStorage and cookies locally.
      For questions, contact us via the <a href="/contact" class="text-(--color-link)">Contact page</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">6. Children</h2>
    <p>
      This site is intended for adults and is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly
      collect data from children.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">7. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. The date at the top of this page reflects the last
      revision. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink)">8. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Privacy questions: <a href="/contact" class="text-(--color-link)">Contact page</a>.
    </p>
  </ProsePage>
</BaseLayout>